The paper deals with algorithms for finding node separators in graphs, which is a problem in graph theory and graph algorithms. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves optimization techniques and local search algorithms, which are relevant to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of graph coarsening and edge ratings suggests relevance to cs.CG (Computational Geometry). Finally, the experiments involve numerical optimization, which is relevant to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
